The paper deals with a fundamental way of comparing evolutionary trees, which is a topic that falls under computational biology. However, the paper focuses on developing computational algorithms for calculating the unrooted subtree prune and regraft (SPR) distance, which is a problem that can be formulated as a graph problem. Therefore, the paper is likely to be categorized under arXiv CS sub-categories that deal with graph algorithms, optimization, and computational complexity. The most likely categories are cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also uses heuristics and search algorithms, which are topics that fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
